IELTS Writing - Task 1 IELTS 5 Test 1
IELTS, English Writing
<p>The line graph depicts the past and projected proportion of population aged 65 and over for a 100 years time span from 1940 to 2040 in three countries, namely Japan, Sweden and the USA.</p>

<p>The most distinguishing feature is that there is an upward trend in the proportion of the senior in all three countries over this period of time. Another interesting observation is that Japan had the lowest proportion of population over 65 and over among the three, but is projected to have the highest property by 2040.</p>

<p>Looking at the details, the proportion of the senior in the USA grows steadily over this period of time, with only a marginal drop between 1980 and 2010. As regards Sweden, the proportion started at approximately 7.5% in 1940 and is estimated to rise to just above 25% in 2040 with fluctuations along the way.</p>

<p>In constrast, the proportion of the senior people in Japan dropped slightly from 5% in 1940 to around 3% in 1960 and then remained constant until around 1990. The figure then rose with an increasing speed and is projected to skyrocket from 10% in 2020 to 25% in 2040, outstripping the senior proportion in the other two countries.</p>

<p>(202 words)</p>